Police at the weekend arraigned a loan officer, Komolafe Ariyo and a branch manager, Ademiluyi Adebanjo in an Abeokuta Magistrate’s Court sitting in Isabo for allegedly stealing N9.5 million from ASIEA Microfinance Bank. Ariyo, 38 and Adebanjo, 35 were charged with five counts of conspiracy and stealing. Prosecution lawyer, Insp. Lawrence Olu-Balogun, told the court that the defendants who committed the offence on 8th March, 2019 at ASIEA Microfinance Bank in Amolaso area of Abeokuta allegedly converted N9.4 million belonging to the bank to their personal use. The prosecutor said that Komolafe allegedly stole N2. 6 million while Adebanjo stole N6.84million. The prosecutor said the offence contravened provisions of Sections 390(9); 419; and 516 of the Criminal Code Laws of Ogun 2006. The defendants, however, pleaded not guilty to the charge. Magistrate Olakulehin Oke admitted the defendants to bail in the sum of N1million each with two sureties in like sum. Oke ordered that the sureties must reside within the court’s jurisdiction and must show evidence of tax payment to Ogun State Government. He adjourned the case until May 24 for trial.